extend layout 

block content
    img(src="img/courses/product-dev-header.png", alt="")
    .course-nav
        h6 
            a(href="/") Home >
            a(href="/our-academy")  Course >
            a(href=`${url}`)  #{title}
    .container 
        .full-business-analysis-page
            .business-analysis-cover
                .business-analysis-div1
                    img(src="img/courses/product-dev-banner.png", alt="analysis-banner")
                    
                .business-analysis-div2
                    h2(style="text-align: center; font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px") PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT 
                        br
                        |(WEB & MOBILE) 
                    p Product Development is the journey of translating an idea from conception to its final launch. This is a relevant role in many organizations because it focuses on providing new value to existing and potential customers.                    
                    a(href="/enrol") 
                        | 
                        button Enrol Now
                    p(style=".d-inline-flex.gap-1; color: #2c2b5e; font-weight: bold") Course Modules 
                        a(data-bs-toggle='collapse', href='#collapseExample', role='button', aria-expanded='false', aria-controls='collapseExample')
                            i.fa.fa-caret-down(aria-hidden='true')
                        #collapseExample.collapse
                            .card.card-body(style="")
                                ol(style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 10px")
                                    li Introduction to Product Development         
                                    li Idea Generation and Conceptualization
                                    li Market Research and Validation
                                    li Product Design and Prototyping
                                    li Lean and Agile Principles  
                                    li Business Model Canvas and Value Proposition
                                    li Product Roadmapping and Planning
                                    li Cross-functional Collaboration
                                    li Product Launch and Marketing
                                    li User Feedback and Iteration
                                    li Scaling and Growth Strategies
                                    li Measuring Success and Metrics
                                    li Product Lifecycle Management
                                    li Real-world Case Studies and Exercises
        
        .container 
            .business-analysis-cover(style="color:black")
                .business-analysis-div1(style="margin-right: 60px")
                    h2 Course Overview: 
                    p(style="margin-top: 15px") This course will focus on implementing a product life cycle from design to retirement. You will acquire skills in product development, vision, and strategy required to excel in this dynamic role. 

                .business-analysis-div2
                    h2 Who is this course for?
                    p 
                        ul(style="list-style-type: disc;line-height: 25px; margin-top: 10px") 
                            li Individuals who want to build their skill set in Product Development
                            li Working Professionals who want to transition into a Product Development role.
                            li Individuals who want to transition into a ‘no-coding’ Tech role.

        .container 
            .why-choose(style="color:black")     
                h2 Why Choose Our Product Development Course?
                ul
                    li Expert Instructors: Learn from experienced Business Analysts with real-world expertise.
                    li Practical Learning: Gain hands-on experience through involvement in real-life scenarios.
                    li Networking: Connect with industry professionals and peers.
                    li Career Support: Access resources for job placement and career progression.
                    li Instructor-Led Live classes: Experience personalized learning and receive immediate feedback from Instructors.                   
                
                h6 Join our Product Development course and embark on a journey to become skilled in Product Development, 
                    br 
                    |equipped to collaborate with Agile teams to deliver exceptional products and drive business success.
                
                h6(style="padding-top: 20px") The course duration: 8 weeks
                    br
                    |Start Date: To be communicated
                    br
                    |Course Fee: £500/N450,000
                    br
                    |Course Level: Beginner
                    br
                    |Certificate of Completion: YES
    
